/**
 * @class btkSetPointValues
 * @brief Sets point's coordinates (values) from a matrix
 * @syntax{%btkSetPointValues(h\, index\, v)\n %btkSetPointValues(h\, label\, v)}
 * @param h Handle pointing to a C++ btk::Acquisition object.
 * @param index Integer containing the index of the point to modify.
 * @param label String containing the label of the point to modify.
 * @param v Matrix of reals where the number of rows corresponds to the number of frames in the acquisition and the number of columns corresponds to the components of the point.
 *
 * @par Detailed description:
 * To modify only the value of a specific type of point (angles, forces, moments, ...) you can use
 * use the following duos:
 *   - btkGetAnglesValues / btkSetAnglesValues ;
 *   - btkGetForcesValues / btkSetForcesValues ;
 *   - btkGetMarkersValues / btkSetMarkersValues ;
 *   - btkGetMomentsValues / btkSetMomentsValues ;
 *   - btkGetPowersValues / btkSetPowersValues ;
 *   - btkGetScalarsValues / btkSetScalarsValues.
 *
 * @sa btkGetPointsResiduals, btkGetPointsValues, btkGetPoints, btkSetPointsResiduals
 * @ingroup BTKMatlabPointModifier
 */